# iOS Shell

- `ios/app` is a SwiftUI shell over shared framework exports with bridge facades from `kmp/bridge-apple`.
- Keep native SwiftUI views, project generation, and Apple integration details here.
- Prefer consuming shared state through the existing Apple bridge instead of duplicating domain logic in Swift.
- If the shell needs new shared behavior, adjust shared bridge annotations/codegen flow rather than creating Swift-only source of truth.
- Ensure lifecycle teardown is explicit: call `rootComponent.destroy()` in `deinit`.
- Check `ios/app/README.md` before changing framework build or project generation steps.
